summary: The document is an FBI identification form from the JFK assassination records collection, dated January 15, 1999. It details the agency (FBI), record numbers, and document specifics including originator, recipients, title, date, and subjects. Marked as 'UNCLASSIFIED', it was released with certain deletions. It references individuals such as Mr. Belmont, Mr. Mohr, and Mr. Casper, alongside activities linked to Rosselli in Los Angeles, including his residence and appearances at the Friar's Club in Beverly Hills. Additionally, it notes the IRS's involvement under JFK Law 11(a).
key_findings: Document is part of the JFK Assassination Records Collection.
FBI document with record numbers and series details.
Mentions individuals and activities related to Rosselli in Los Angeles.
References IRS involvement under JFK Law 11(a).
Document status is 'UNCLASSIFIED' but released with deletions.
